    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my monstera deliciosa is acting weird. the bottom leaves are turning yellow and they have some pretty dark brown spots on them. i water it about once a week and it gets decent indirect light near a window. id satisfy the drainage too, but i'm worried something is wrong. what could be causing this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your Monstera deliciosa might be experiencing a bit of a case of the \"yellow and brown leaf syndrome.\" This can be caused by a few different things, but don't worry, it's usually not too serious. First, let's check your watering schedule. Even though you're watering once a week, it's possible that the plant's needs have changed, especially if it's grown larger or if the weather has gotten warmer. Think of it as your plant's way of saying, \"Hey, I'm feeling a bit thirsty!\" Make sure the soil is dry to the touch before you water again. Also, ensure that your plant isn't sitting in water, as that can lead to root rot. You might also want to check for pests, as they can sometimes cause discoloration and spots. A little bit of a pest check won't hurt, right? Just make sure to treat any issues promptly. And remember, Monstera deliciosa is a bit like a mischievous goblin; it loves a bit of attention and care, but it can also be a bit of a handful. Keep an eye on it, and it should bounce back in no time!",
